## Description

Hi, I noticed that nested ul in content block look kind of strange. 

> [!NOTE]
> In the bottom right corner of the images is the html element and its
> css rules.

## Actual Behavior

When I inspect the rules, I can see that this rule has precendence.

    .content ul:not(:first-child) {
        margin-top: 1em;
    }

![wrong](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/60de00d0-3b48-4f13-b111-58bbc767a3eb)

## Expected Behavior

There is another rule that seems actually reasonable. If I deactive
above rule, it takes action.

    .content ul ul {
        list-style-type: circle;
        margin-bottom: .25em;
        margin-top: .25em;
    }

![right](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/4968be5b-4024-4c66-ac76-5e64ff0a434f)
